What is the formula to calculate the area of the ellipse tray?
The area of an ellipse is given by the formula A = πab, where a and b are the semi-major and semi-minor axes of the ellipse, respectively.

<image>
What is the formula to calculate the area of the square tray?
The area of a square is given by the formula A = side^2, where 'side' is the length of one side of the square.

<image>
How do you calculate the ratio of the area of an ellipse tray to a square tray?
The ratio of the area of an ellipse tray to a square tray can be calculated by dividing the area of the ellipse by the area of the square. Thus, the ratio is (πab) / (side^2).

<image>
If an ellipse tray has a semi-major axis of length a and a semi-minor axis of length b, and the side of the square tray is s, what is the formula to find the number of ellipse trays needed to form a square tray?
The number of ellipse trays needed can be found using the formula: N = (s^2) / (πab), where N is the number of ellipse trays.
